[1] Belgium, additional cases
Date: Fri 5 Oct 2018
Source: dhnet (Belgium) [in French, machine transl., edited]
http://www.dhnet.be/regions/luxembourg/peste-porcine-africaine-44-sangliers-controles-positifs-5bb7883dcd70a16d813b411d


Rene Collin, the Walloon Minister for Agriculture, Nature and Forests, has received from the Wildlife Surveillance Network in Wallonia a new inventory of tests carried out in the framework of the management of African swine fever in the defined territory of 63 000 hectares (630 square km; 243 square miles).

To date, 106 wild boars have been collected. A total of 80 of them were found within the perimeter. Of these, there are now 44 viropositive cases. The wild boars collected outside the perimeter were all negative. The number of boars tested positive continues to increase. Indeed, while there were 28 [on Tue 2 Oct 2018] and 32 [on Thu 4 Oct 2018], there are now 12 more.

